Each chord drifts slightly out of tune — G flattened by 20 cents, A sharpened by 20 cents — creating a dragging, elastic groove.
The drums hit late and swing with mechanical tension. Bass follows loosely behind, giving a sense of unstable motion.
Guitars sound raw, overdriven, and alive, like metal scraping through the mix. offbeat.

A melancholic grunge progression (E5–A5–G#5–F5) performed in microtonal tuning.
G# is slightly lowered by 40 cents, breaking the perfect resolution to F.
The guitars sound hollow and emotional, drums drag behind the beat, and vocals carry exhaustion.
The track should feel unresolved — half-asleep. offbeat.




